And that Meth
                                 •
                              salah's daies thou wer't to live;

div.p:
                           Blessed is the man that feareth alwaie. If thou would'st beget true fear in heart, learn of the wise man, Prov. 2.3, 4, 5. Incline thy ear to wisdom, and applie thy heart to understanding. Crie after knowledg, seek her as silver, and search for her as hid treasure. Then thou shalt understand the fear of the Lord. Whose word thou maiest take, and finde the knowledg of God, to fear him truly alwaie.


True fear great joie doth bring, it makes thee bold;

All slavish fear to slight, thy faith to hold.
